\begin{abstract}
We use the empirical evidence that F-spin multiplets exist in nuclei for 
only selected states as an indication that F-spin can be regarded as 
a partial symmetry.
We show that there is a class of non-F-scalar IBM-2 
Hamiltonians with partial F-spin symmetry, which reproduce the known 
systematics of collective bands in nuclei.  
These Hamiltonians predict that the scissors states have good F-spin and 
form F-spin multiplets, which is supported by the existing data.  
\end{abstract}
